Package src

Class BinaryTree<T>

java.lang.Object
src.BinaryTree<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
BinaryTreeInterface<T>, TreeInterface<T>
public class BinaryTree<T> extends Object implements BinaryTreeInterface<T>
This is the BinaryTree class which contains definitions of a BinaryTree and implements the BinaryTreeInterface A BinaryTree is just composed of a single BinaryNode, root, which is linked up to the rest of the tree. This 'root' BinaryNode is linked to all of the subnodes (which are also BinaryNodes) of the BinaryTree. Essentially, a BinaryTree is made up of many nodes, but we only reference the root node. This class is composed of similar methods to those in the BinaryNode class, but also has a constructor to create a tree based on two traversal strings (preorder and inorder), and a method to add a left and right subtree to the root node. Each method is documented separately.
Version:
3.0
Author:
George Matta, Pierlorenzo Peruzzo, Matt Dong
